.TH 9p-getattr 5 "@META_DATE@" "@META_ALIAS@" "@META_NAME@"
.SH NAME
9p getattr \- get file status
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
size[4] Tgetattr tag[2] fid[4] request_mask[8]
size[4] Rgetattr tag[2] response_mask[8] lstat[n]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
The getattr transaction inquires about the file identified by fid.
The reply will contain a machine-independent directory entry,
laid out as follows.  Only fields with appropriate bit set in
request_mask[8] need be returned.  Similarly, response_mask[8]
indicates which fields are valid in the response.
See below for bit values.
.TP
\fIst_result_mask[8]\fR
A bitmask indicating which fields in the response are valid.
See below for bit values.
.TP
\fIqid.type[1]\fR
the type of the file (directory, etc.), represented as a bit
vector corresponding to the high 8 bits of the file's mode word.
.br
Valid if bit P9_STATS_INO (0x100) is set in result_mask[8].
.TP
\fIqid.vers[4]\fR
version number for given path.
.br
Valid if bit P9_STATS_INO (0x0100) is set in result_mask[8].
.TP
\fIqid.path[8]\fR
the file server's unique identification for the file
.br
Valid if bit P9_STATS_INO (0x0100) is set in result_mask[8].
.TP
\fIst_mode[4]\fR
Permission and flags
.br
Valid if bit P9_STATS_MODE (0x0001) is set in result_mask[8].
.TP
\fIst_nlink[8]\fR
Number of hard links
.br
Valid if bit P9_STATS_NLINK (0x0002) is set in result_mask[8].
.TP
\fIst_uid[4]\fR
User id of owner
.br
Valid if bit P9_STATS_UID (0x0004) is set in result_mask[8].
.TP
\fIst_gid[4]\fR
Group ID of owner
.br
Valid if bit P9_STATS_GID (0x0008) is set in result_mask[8].
.TP
\fIst_rdev[8]\fR
Device ID (if special file)
.br
Valid if bit P9_STATS_RDEV (0x0010) is set in result_mask[8].
.TP
\fIst_size[8]\fR
Size, in bytes
.br
Valid if bit P9_STATS_SIZE (0x0200) is set in result_mask[8].
.TP
\fIst_blksize[8]\fR
Block size for file system IO.
.br
Always must be valid (no mask bit).
.TP
\fIst_blocks[8]\fR
Number of file system blocks allocated
.br
Valid if bit P9_STATS_BLOCKS (0x0400) is set in result_mask[8].
.TP
\fIst_atime_sec[8]\fR
Time of last access, seconds
.br
Valid if bit P9_STATS_ATIME (0x0020) is set in result_mask[8].
.TP
\fIst_atime_nsec[8]\fR
Time of last access, nanoseconds
.br
Valid if bit P9_STATS_ATIME (0x0020) is set in result_mask[8].
.TP
\fIst_mtime_sec[8]\fR
Time of last modification, seconds
.br
Valid if bit P9_STATS_MTIME (0x0040) is set in result_mask[8].
.TP
\fIst_mtime_nsec[8]\fR
Time of last modification, nanoseconds
.br
Valid if bit P9_STATS_MTIME (0x0040) is set in result_mask[8].
.TP
\fIst_ctime_sec[8]\fR
Time of last status change, seconds
.br
Valid if bit P9_STATS_CTIME (0x0080) is set in result_mask[8].
.TP
\fIst_ctime_nsec[8]\fR
Time of last status change, nanoseconds
.br
Valid if bit P9_STATS_CTIME (0x0080) is set in result_mask[8].
.TP
\fIst_btime_sec[8]\fR
Reserved for future use.
.br
Valid if bit P9_STATS_BTIME (0x0800) is set in result_mask[8].
.TP
\fIst_btime_nsec[8]\fR
Reserved for future use.
.br
Valid if bit P9_STATS_BTIME (0x0800) is set in result_mask[8].
.TP
\fIst_gen[8]\fR
Inode generation number.
.br
Valid if bit P9_STATS_GEN (0x1000) is set in result_mask[8].
.TP
\fIst_data_version[8]\fR
Reserved for future use.
.br
Valid if bit P9_STATS_DATA_VERSION (0x2000) is set in result_mask[8].
.SH ORIGIN
9P2000.L
.SH SEE ALSO
9p-intro(5)
